 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "# ATCO2 Gold Annotation Extractor\n\nExtracts gold-standard transcripts from ATCO2 XML annotation files\nand saves the result as `atco2_gold_clean.csv`.\n\n**Input**  \n- `ATCO2-ASRdataset-v1_beta.tgz` — original ATCO2 corpus archive  \n\n**Output**  \n- `atco2_gold_clean.csv` with columns:\n  `file`, `segment_id`, `start`, `end`, `gold_text`, `gold_clean_text`\n\n`gold_text` preserves entity tags (e.g. `[#callsign]...[/#callsign]`).  \n`gold_clean_text` strips all tags, leaving plain spoken-form text."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "import os\nimport re\nimport tarfile\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\nimport pandas as pd"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Configuration\n\nSet the path to the ATCO2 archive and the desired output file name."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "# Path to the ATCO2 corpus archive\nTGZ_PATH    = 'ATCO2-ASRdataset-v1_beta.tgz'\nOUTPUT_CSV  = 'atco2_gold_clean.csv'\n\n# Extraction filter: only include segments with correct_transcript == 1\n# Set to False to include all segments regardless of annotation quality\nFILTER_CORRECT_TRANSCRIPT = True\n\nassert os.path.exists(TGZ_PATH), f'Archive not found: {TGZ_PATH}'\nprint(f'Archive found: {TGZ_PATH}')"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## XML Parsing\n\nEach XML file corresponds to one recording.  \nThe structure per segment is:\n\n```xml\n<segment>\n  <start>0.0</start>\n  <end>3.77</end>\n  <speaker>A</speaker>\n  <text>[#callsign]Swiss Two Zero Four[/#callsign] climb ...</text>\n  <tags>\n    <correct_transcript>1</correct_transcript>\n  </tags>\n</segment>\n```\n\n`correct_transcript=1` means the transcript was verified by an annotator.  \nSegments with `correct_transcript=0` are noisy and excluded by default."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "def strip_entity_tags(text: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Remove ATCO2 entity tags, returning plain spoken-form text.\n\n    Example:\n        '[#callsign]Swiss Two Zero Four[/#callsign] climb'\n        -> 'Swiss Two Zero Four climb'\n    \"\"\"\n    return re.sub(r'\\[/?#[a-z_]+\\]', '', text).strip()\n\n\ndef parse_xml(xml_bytes: bytes, filename: str) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Parse one ATCO2 XML file and return a list of segment records.\"\"\"\n    records = []\n    try:\n        root = ET.fromstring(xml_bytes)\n    except ET.ParseError as e:\n        print(f'  [WARN] XML parse error in {filename}: {e}')\n        return records\n\n    for seg_id, seg in enumerate(root.findall('segment')):\n        start = seg.findtext('start', default='')\n        end   = seg.findtext('end',   default='')\n        text  = seg.findtext('text',  default='').strip()\n\n        tags = seg.find('tags')\n        correct_transcript = 0\n        if tags is not None:\n            val = tags.findtext('correct_transcript', default='0')\n            correct_transcript = int(val) if val.isdigit() else 0\n\n        if FILTER_CORRECT_TRANSCRIPT and correct_transcript != 1:\n            continue\n\n        records.append({\n            'file':            filename,\n            'segment_id':      seg_id,\n            'start':           float(start) if start else None,\n            'end':             float(end)   if end   else None,\n            'gold_text':       text,\n            'gold_clean_text': strip_entity_tags(text),\n        })\n    return records"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Extract from Archive\n\nIterates over all 560 XML files in the `.tgz` archive without\nextracting the full archive to disk."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "all_records = []\n\nwith tarfile.open(TGZ_PATH, 'r:gz') as tar:\n    xml_members = [m for m in tar.getmembers() if m.name.endswith('.xml')]\n    print(f'Found {len(xml_members)} XML files')\n\n    for member in xml_members:\n        filename = os.path.basename(member.name)\n        f = tar.extractfile(member)\n        if f is None:\n            continue\n        xml_bytes = f.read()\n        records = parse_xml(xml_bytes, filename)\n        all_records.extend(records)\n\nprint(f'Total segments extracted: {len(all_records)}')"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Build DataFrame"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "df = pd.DataFrame(all_records, columns=[\n    'file', 'segment_id', 'start', 'end', 'gold_text', 'gold_clean_text'\n])\n\nprint(f'Shape: {df.shape}')\nprint(f'Unique files: {df[\"file\"].nunique()}')\nprint()\ndf.head(5)"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Quality Check\n\nVerify there are no empty transcripts and inspect segment length distribution."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "empty_gold = df['gold_clean_text'].str.strip().eq('').sum()\nprint(f'Empty gold_clean_text rows: {empty_gold}')\n\ndf['word_count'] = df['gold_clean_text'].str.split().str.len()\nprint()\nprint(df['word_count'].describe().round(2))"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Save Output"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "df.drop(columns=['word_count'], inplace=True, errors='ignore')\ndf.to_csv(OUTPUT_CSV, index=False)\nprint(f'Saved {len(df)} rows to {OUTPUT_CSV}')\n\n# Verify round-trip\ndf_check = pd.read_csv(OUTPUT_CSV)\nprint(f'Verification read: {df_check.shape}')\ndf_check.head(3)"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Sample Output\n\nPreview a few rows to confirm entity tag stripping."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "for _, row in df.sample(n=3, random_state=42).iterrows():\n    print('file      :', row['file'])\n    print('gold_text :', row['gold_text'][:120])\n    print('clean     :', row['gold_clean_text'][:120])\n    print()"
  }
 ]
}
